Brussel mr. Joseph Sabbarton
I have reed the 2 packetts, & past all in conformitre, for want of time have not sont you the
copie of what you signed, mine I exspect from you as also towards a sunday some of
the parcell laces mentioned &my formar. inclosed a loder from m. Collier, which pray
deliver to m. vale, I do supose that mr. follier will come over speedly, I have a letter from
m. Maynard, by which he desires mee to step over to you to consult aboue the bustynes
wil Il., I finde chere is noting to be don, butt what you ae att, & endeavor with
dusheurel to opose jacobs, of I can be assitent please to command
yd sack shall be sent to m. vander Borght foulded in a cougle of bayes, & to shall
alwayes beable to returne itt inthoum charge

7 onclithat I desire imeseed of 35 duble reds butt 20 in all amonghst them the
formar assortment, so that not above 12 a 15 p of Â£8.10 a Â£90 ps must be, because I have

I hope you shall be able to gett the in ordered kersies aboard smish, pray dispatch with all

I perceeave that you much
feare, of my bills on H.C. to be complyed with, of which one was due 21 agl yd. stile
